de.unistuttgart.vis.wearable.os.storage

Class SensorDataDeSerializer

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.unistuttgart.vis.wearable.os.storage.SensorDataDeSerializer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class SensorDataDeSerializer
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable

    This deserializer reads data from a file and creates an object for the data. The file to read should have been created using the SensorDataSerializer class

    Note: This class executes asynchronously.

    Author:
    roehrdor

    • Constructor Detail

      • SensorDataDeSerializer

        public SensorDataDeSerializer(int sensorID,
                              java.util.List<SensorData> sensorData,
                              int noDatasetsToRead)
        Create a new deserialized object that reads the given number of data sets from the file and inserts them into the given sensor Data list. If the file contains less than noDatasetsToRead all the values from the file will be deserialized.
        Parameters:
        sensorID - the sensor if to read the data for
        sensorData - the list to insert the data into
        noDatasetsToRead - the number of element to be deserialized. This number needs to be at least 1, ohterwise an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if less than one element shall be read

      • SensorDataDeSerializer

        public SensorDataDeSerializer(int sensorID,
                              java.util.List<SensorData> sensorData,
                              int noDatasetsToRead,
                              long startTime)
        Create a new deserialized object that reads the beginning from the start time the given number of datasets into the given Data list. If the start time is older than the oldest available data field in the file the reading process starts by the oldest one.
        Parameters:
        sensorID - the sensor if to read the data for
        sensorData - the list to insert the data into
        noDatasetsToRead - the number of element to be deserialized. This number needs to be at least 1, ohterwise an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown
        startTime - the oldest data set to be read
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if noDatasetsToRead is less than 1

      • SensorDataDeSerializer

        public SensorDataDeSerializer(int sensorID,
                              java.util.List<SensorData> sensorData,
                              long startTime,
                              long endTime,
                              int maxNumberOfValues)
        Create a new deserialized object that reads the beginning from the start time stamp to the end time stamp. This procedure can also be limited to not to read too many data sections. The range returned can be expressed with [starTime, endTime)
        Parameters:
        sensorID - the sensor if to read the data for
        sensorData - the list to insert the data into
        startTime - the oldest data to be read
        endTime - anything before this data will be read
        maxNumberOfValues - is the maximum amount of data sets to be read. If this is set to 0 there will be no limit and all found data will be read
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if maxNumberOfValues is less than 0

    • Method Detail

      • work

        public long work()
        Start the deserialization process. This procedure will execute asynchronously and return a worker ID. By calling jobFinsihed(long) it can be checked whether the job has terminated or is still running.
        Returns:
        the worker id for the current job

      • jobFinsihed

        public static boolean jobFinsihed(long id)

        Check whether the current job is still running or has already finished executing.

        Note for any random value that is no worker id this function will return true. So if this function returns false the job is still running, otherwise there is no job with the given id or the job has already been finished.

        Parameters:
        id - the id of the worker
        Returns:
        false if the job is still running, true otherwise
